<TITLE> 50 injured in Islamist group's clashes with police </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 10 (bdnews24.com)More than 50 people including policemen were injured in clashes between law enforcers and members of the Islami Chhatra Majlish in the Baitul Mukarram Mosque area Thursday. Angry members of the Islamist outfit set two police motorcycles ablaze. Traffic at the Paltan crossing remained suspended for about half an hour. Contacted, Paltan police chief Farid Ahmed told bdnews24.com: "About 50 people including police officers were injured. Two police motorbikes were set on fire." A bdnews24.com photographer reported from the scene that police had obstructed the Islami Chhatra Majlish men when they wanted to move out of the Baitul Mukarram Mosque after Zohr prayers to submit a memorandum to the chief adviser demanding cancellation of the National Women's Development Policy. At the time, the leaders and workers of the Islamist outfit attacked the police triggering clashes, witnesses said. A number of vehicles were ransacked. The Baitul Mukarram market had remained briefly closed. bdnews24.com
